                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/737a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in Allied Countries</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d219fn1">Also to the Chargé in Siam, the Chargé in Rumania,
                        and the Special Agent in Corfu, Aug. 20, 4 p.m. (File No.
                        763.72119/742a.)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-18T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 18, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Please ascertain as promptly as possible the views of the Government to which you
                    are accredited in regard to the Pope’s recent peace communication. The above
                    information is desired by the President. Cable reply, which will be treated as
                    strictly confidential.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
